The Lagos State Police Command on Wednesday said it has arrested more suspects in the murder of Chief Executive Officer of Super TV, Usifo Ataga, as an “afterthought”. The Lagos State Commissioner of Police, Hakeem Odumosu, on Wednesday said it has also established a “conspiracy” in the circumstances surrounding the killing of Ataga. Usifo Ataga: Family reveals how Chidinma, other accomplices killed Super TV CEO Odumosu said the slain Ataga was said to be drugged before he was killed. He also denied the claims that the police were trying to create a soft landing for the suspect, Chidinma. CP Odumosu said, “We have established a case of conspiracy in the murder and we have arrested more suspects.” Usifo Ataga: Chidinma exhibits trait of an active criminal – Police reacts to new claims